    "en": {
      "title": "A New York minor contracted monkeypox",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "New York State's first case of monkeypox has been reported in a minor under the age of 18, according to a weekly summary from the New York State Department of Health.",
        "The week ending Wednesday and few other details were provided in the report released Friday to protect the privacy of the patient's family.",
        "The child is known to live outside New York City. It is a hot spot for this epidemic. Nine other cases involving children are currently being reported in the United States.",
        "Monkeypox is currently more concentrated among gay men with multiple sex partners.",
        "The CDC reported last week that 99% of patients were men and 94% had recently had sex with men. However, the latest figures from New York include two women, as well as three who identify as transgender or non-binary, and three who are simply listed as unknown."
      ],
